---
import TopicLayout from '../../components/TopicLayout.astro';

const exampleQuestions = [
  'How are enterprise SaaS companies integrating AI?',
  'What is the best AI pricing strategy for B2B software?',
  'Which companies are winning the enterprise AI market?',
  'How should I evaluate AI vendors for my organization?',
];

const relatedTopics = [
  { title: 'AI Strategy', href: '/topics/ai-strategy' },
  { title: 'AI Agents', href: '/topics/ai-agents' },
  { title: 'Context Engineering', href: '/topics/context-engineering' },
  { title: 'Vibe Coding', href: '/topics/vibe-coding' },
];
---

<TopicLayout
  title="Enterprise AI"
  metaTitle="Enterprise SaaS in the AI Era — AmbitiousOS"
  metaDescription="How enterprise software companies are integrating AI, pricing strategies, vendor evaluation, and market dynamics. Research from Reading Ambitiously."
  headline="Enterprise SaaS in the AI Era"
  intro="The enterprise software landscape is being reshaped by AI. Every major SaaS company — from Salesforce to ServiceNow to Palantir — is racing to embed AI into their products. The winners will be defined by execution, not just features."
  exampleQuestions={exampleQuestions}
  relatedTopics={relatedTopics}
>
  <p>
    The shift from seat-based pricing to consumption-based and outcome-based models is creating
    new economics for software companies. AI copilots, agents, and automation are simultaneously
    expanding total addressable markets while threatening incumbent revenue streams. Understanding
    these dynamics is critical for anyone building, buying, or investing in enterprise software.
  </p>
  <p>
    Reading Ambitiously has tracked this transformation across 64+ editions — covering earnings
    calls, product launches, strategic pivots, and the companies that are getting it right.
    AmbitiousOS connects all of this research through an interactive knowledge graph so you can
    explore the relationships between companies, strategies, and market dynamics.
  </p>
</TopicLayout>
